Title: Diagnosis of test `testBug545`
Details: The test `testBug545` in the `InlineObjectLiteralsTest` class is failing. The test is checking the behavior of splitting an object literal into individual variables and updating all uses. However, the test is encountering an error due to an internal compiler error.

Based on the call stack, the error occurred in the method `InlineObjectLiterals.InliningBehavior.splitObject`. This method is responsible for splitting the object literal into individual variables and updating all uses. The method first computes the set of possible keys for the object literal and then iterates over each key to create a new variable node and replace the corresponding references.

There is no specific JavaDoc documentation available for this method, but based on the code comments, we can understand that the method splits up the object literal into individual variables and updates all uses.

It is likely that the error occurred due to a bug in the logic of splitting the object literal or updating the references.

Suggested fix:
- The issue needs to be investigated further to identify the root cause and fix it accordingly. It may require analyzing the specific inputs that cause the internal compiler error and debugging the logic of splitting the object literal and updating the references in the `splitObject` method of the `InlineObjectLiterals.InliningBehavior` class.

Note: It is recommended to consult the developer or the documentation of the system under test for a more accurate diagnosis and solution.
